The paper presents a new high-level engine for graph processing that supports a query language similar to datalog, which suggests that it could fall under the categories of databases (cs.DB) or data structures (cs.DS). The paper also discusses the use of join algorithms and query optimization, which are common topics in distributed computing (cs.DC) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper presents performance benchmarks and comparisons with other graph processing engines, which could fall under the category of machine learning (cs.LG).
